## Key Conventions

- **Import alias**: Use `@/*` or configured path alias for imports. Avoid deep relative paths.
- **Component organization** — organize by what the component IS:
  - `ui/` — UI library primitives (READ-ONLY if using shadcn/ui)
  - `sidebar/` — shell navigation (sidebar, header)
  - `cards/` — reusable card components
  - `banners/` — hero/banner sections
  - `widgets/` — floating/interactive widgets
  - `sections/` — page sections that compose cards/banners
  - `pages/` — full page-level content views
  - `modal/` — modal dialogs
  - Think about what the component IS, not what page it appears on.
{{#IF_SHADCN}}
- **`src/components/ui/` is READ-ONLY** — never modify UI library primitives directly. Create wrappers in feature directories that import and extend them.
{{/IF_SHADCN}}
{{#IF_ZOD}}
- **Form validation**: All Zod schemas go in a dedicated validation directory. Never define validation inline in components.
{{/IF_ZOD}}
{{#IF_NICE_MODAL}}
- **Modals**: Use `@ebay/nice-modal-react` with centralized `ModalConstant` for IDs. Each modal uses `NiceModal.create()` + UI Dialog. Register in barrel file.
{{/IF_NICE_MODAL}}
{{#IF_NEXTJS}}
- **Routing**: Each major section should be a page route. Layouts provide persistent shells. Use `usePathname()` + `<Link>` for navigation.
{{/IF_NEXTJS}}

{{#IF_RTK_QUERY}}
## Service Layer

- **`src/services/api/`** — RTK Query services ONLY. Each file extends the base API factory. One service per domain.
- **Base service** — Network setup only (JWT injection, error handling). Do NOT add business logic.
- **Service registry** — When adding a new service, register in 3 places: reducers, middleware, and re-export.
- **Tag constants** — All RTK cache tags in a centralized constant file. Never define tags inline. Use `Object.values()` for tag arrays.
- **Request/Response types** — All DTOs in dedicated model directories. Never define types inline in service files.
- **Service wrappers** — Optional convenience hooks wrapping RTK mutations. Only create when the same logic is reused across components.
{{/IF_RTK_QUERY}}

{{#IF_NESTJS}}
## Backend Conventions

- **Module structure**: One module per domain. Each module has controller, service, and DTOs.
- **DTOs**: All in dedicated DTO files with class-validator decorators. Never accept raw objects.
- **Guards**: Use guards for auth. Mark public endpoints explicitly.
- **Pipes**: Use ValidationPipe globally. DTOs handle validation.
- **Interceptors**: Use for response transformation and logging.
{{/IF_NESTJS}}

{{#IF_PYTHON}}
## Python Conventions

- **Type hints**: Use type hints on all function signatures. Use `from __future__ import annotations` for modern syntax.
- **Imports**: Group imports in order: stdlib, third-party, local. Use absolute imports.
- **Virtual environments**: Always use `venv` or `poetry` for dependency isolation.
{{/IF_PYTHON}}

{{#IF_DJANGO}}
## Django Conventions

- **Models**: One model per concept. Use `Meta` class for ordering, constraints. Always add `__str__`.
- **Migrations**: Run `makemigrations` after model changes. Never edit migrations manually.
- **Views**: Prefer class-based views (CBV) for CRUD, function-based views (FBV) for custom logic.
- **URLs**: Use `path()` with named routes. Namespace per app.
- **Settings**: Use environment variables for secrets. Split settings into base/dev/prod.
- **Serializers**: All DRF serializers in dedicated `serializers.py`. Never define inline.
- **Management commands**: Custom commands go in `management/commands/`.
{{/IF_DJANGO}}

{{#IF_FASTAPI}}
## FastAPI Conventions

- **Routers**: One router per domain in `routers/` directory. Register in `app.include_router()`.
- **Pydantic models**: All request/response schemas in `schemas/`. Never define inline.
- **Dependency injection**: Use `Depends()` for shared logic (auth, db sessions).
- **Async**: Use `async def` for I/O-bound endpoints. Use sync for CPU-bound.
- **Error handling**: Raise `HTTPException` with specific status codes. Use custom exception handlers for domain errors.
{{/IF_FASTAPI}}

{{#IF_FLASK}}
## Flask Conventions

- **Blueprints**: One blueprint per feature domain. Register in app factory.
- **App factory**: Use `create_app()` pattern for configuration.
- **Routes**: Group related routes in blueprints. Use `url_for()` for URL generation.
- **Config**: Use class-based config (Development, Production, Testing).
{{/IF_FLASK}}

{{#IF_PHP}}
## PHP Conventions

- **PSR-4 autoloading**: Follow namespace-to-directory mapping. One class per file.
- **PSR-12 coding style**: Follow standard coding style. Use automated formatters.
- **Type declarations**: Use strict types (`declare(strict_types=1)`) in all files. Type all parameters, returns, and properties.
- **Never use raw superglobals**: Use framework Request objects instead of `$_GET`, `$_POST`, `$_REQUEST`.
{{/IF_PHP}}

{{#IF_LARAVEL}}
## Laravel Conventions

- **Eloquent models**: One model per table. Define `$fillable` or `$guarded`. Use relationships and scopes.
- **Migrations**: Use artisan to generate. Never edit existing migrations in production — create new ones.
- **Controllers**: One resource controller per model. Use Form Requests for validation.
- **Form Requests**: All validation in dedicated Form Request classes. Never validate in controllers.
- **Resources**: Use API Resources for response transformation. Never return raw models from API endpoints.
- **Artisan commands**: Custom commands in `app/Console/Commands/`. Register in Kernel.
- **Service pattern**: Extract business logic into services. Controllers should only handle HTTP concerns.
- **Blade templates**: Use components and layouts. Avoid inline PHP in views.
{{/IF_LARAVEL}}

{{#IF_SYMFONY}}
## Symfony Conventions

- **Controllers**: Extend `AbstractController`. One controller per feature area.
- **Services**: Register in `services.yaml` or use autowiring. Inject dependencies via constructor.
- **Doctrine entities**: One entity per table. Use repositories for queries.
- **Forms**: Use Form types for validation and data transformation.
- **Twig templates**: Use template inheritance with `extends` and `block`.
{{/IF_SYMFONY}}

## Bug Fixing

Identify the EXACT file and component before patching. After fixing, grep the codebase for similar patterns that may need the same fix.

{{#IF_FRONTEND}}
## Design-to-Code Rules

When building from designs (Figma or .pen files):
- **Never neglect backgrounds** — apply every gradient, color, shadow
- **Always read UI library source** — check for default styles that override yours
- **Exact spacing** — match gap, padding, margin from the design exactly
- **Check every surface** — background, box-shadow, border, border-radius must all match
- **Use design agents** — figma-builder/pen-builder for building, figma-validator/pen-validator for verification
- **Visual compare** — always compare rendered output against the design
{{/IF_FRONTEND}}

